                <note rend="inline" type="source">690d.003/20: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-03-20T11:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1924—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Pending conclusion convention between the United States and France in regard to
                    mandate, French High Commission requests consent of the United States to
                    increase customs duty on alcohol to approximately 50 percent in order to protect
                    the local wine industry which is being injured by spurious concoctions
                    fabricated from imported alcohol. In view of the American regulations governing
                    export of alcohol, I recommend Department accord consent requested. Please reply
                    by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knabenshue</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
